OL,3,CPub body calls for beer duty cut amid
OL,4,Cpotential outdoor smoking ban
OL,6,FShe said: "There is no more meat on
OL,7,Fthe bone to cut, which is why we are
OL,8,Fcalling on the Government reduce the
OL,9,Fcost of doing business so we can
OL,10,Fcontinue to make a massive
OL,11,Fcontribution to the public purse."
OL,13,FPubs and restaurants took a hit during
OL,14,F2020 and 2021, closing for months at a
OL,15,Ftime during Covid-19 lockdowns.
OL,17,FThen, through 2022 and 2023,
OL,18,Fskyrocketing inflation caused their
OL,19,Foperating costs to rise, while the
OL,20,Fcost-of-living crisis depressed sales.
